===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|smilen||to smile|lang=enm}}, of {{etyl|gmq}} origin, from {{da}} {{term|smile||to smile|lang=da}}, from {{non}} *{{term||smīla|to smile|lang=non}}, from {{proto|Germanic|smīlianan||smirōjanan|to smile|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|smeyə-|to laugh, be glad, wonder|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{sv}} {{term|smila||to smile|lang=sv}}, {{gmh}} {{term|smielen||to smile|lang=gmh}}, {{goh}} {{term|smieron|smierōn|to smile|lang=goh}}, {{ang}} {{term|smerian||to laugh at|lang=ang}}, {{ang}} {{term|smercian|lang=ang}}, {{term|smearcian||to smile|lang=ang}}, {{la}} {{term|miror||to wonder at|lang=la}}. More at {{l|en|smirk}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A happy face '''expression''' using mouth, but without producing [[voice]].
#: ''She's got a perfect '''smile'''.''
#: ''He has a sinister '''smile'''.''
#: ''She had a '''smile''' on her face.''
#: ''He always puts a '''smile''' on my face.''

